HEADWORD: brittlebush
<hw>brittlebush</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>fragrant rounded
shrub of SW US and adjacent Mexico having brittle stems and small
crowded blue-green leaves and yellow flowers; produces a resin used in
incense and varnish and in folk medicine.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> brittle bush, incienso, Encelia farinosa.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

